body:
Can we acknowledge that Riot keeps releasing designs both through new champions and reworks, only to dumpster them a week or two later, and call them &#039;impossible to balance&#039;?

Seriously, {{champion:429}} {{champion:266}} {{champion:268}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:163}} {{champion:203}} {{champion:421}} {{champion:72}} {{champion:82}} 

I&#039;m tired of you releasing an &#039;impossible to balance&#039; design, making me fall in love with the character. Then deciding you cannot fix what you created, only to dumpster it for a year or three... We waited since S2 for Yorick, am I going to have to wait 4 years to play Kindred, Aatrox, Azir or Malz again without them being unreliable, overnerfed, pieces of garbage?

The worst part, is when it is a rework... because then you take a long standing champion people already loved, and throw it away, because you wanted to change it, for the sake of change.

And people wonder why I am afraid of a {{champion:102}} rework. They are so hit or miss. Sometimes we get a {{champion:78}} other times a {{champion:82}}
